# Optional: provide a default Google Maps Platform API key so users don't have to
# paste one. The Map Tiles API must be enabled and billing active on the key's
# project. RESTRICT the key by HTTP referrer (your deployed domain) since it is
# shipped to / reachable from the client.
#
# Either variable name works (GOOGLE_MAPS_API_KEY is preferred for hosting dashboards
# like Railway; VITE_GOOGLE_MAPS_API_KEY also works for local Vite dev):
#
#   • Build/dev time  — bakes the key into the bundle (vite reads it via loadEnv).
#   • Railway/runtime — server.js injects GOOGLE_MAPS_API_KEY into the page at request
#                       time, so you can set or rotate it in the dashboard with no rebuild
#                       and without entering it inside the app.
#
# Local dev: copy this file to ".env" and fill it in (".env" is gitignored).
GOOGLE_MAPS_API_KEY=
VITE_GOOGLE_MAPS_API_KEY=
